text: yesterday evening, I went to see this movie at the theater (because my younger brother wanted me to come with him).  And it was a total waste of my money. Absolutely not scary at all. Again : the typical demon possession story.  The storyline was really bad and the filmmakers tried to throw in some humor, but even the jokes failed, as they didn't bring out my ugly laugh. This is the kind of horror that only tries to frighten you by using eerie music or a long silence suddenly followed by extreme loud screams ( & in this movie also Gregorian chant). To shock you and give you a heartattack...But nobody in the cinema room even screamed. I actually fell asleep.  I am easily scared, always have been. 'The ring' gave me the creeps when I was 14 years old. But now I really hope that someone's gonna start making autobiography horror movies about the real monsters that lived and live in this world.
